  "content": {
    "value": {
      "schema": "dast",
      "document": {
        "type": "root",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Terminology"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Applications, Libraries, & Tools"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "The topmost categorization in code is separated into applications, libraries, and tools."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "marks": [
                  "strong"
                ],
                "value": "Tools"
              },
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": " - Developer tooling and custom build commands, generator templates, etc. These should ideally be kept to a minimum, opting to prefer standard tooling where possible."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "marks": [
                  "strong"
                ],
                "value": "Libraries"
              },
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": " - Libraries contain all of the business logic and feature code. The majority of a codebase should consist of domain-specific libraries."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "marks": [
                  "strong"
                ],
                "value": "Applications"
              },
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": " - Applications contain little code, and are mostly responsible for providing a runtime with some type of configuration."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Monorepo"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Not to be confused with a monolith, a monorepo is a collection of libraries, applications, and tools that share a single source repository. Together they represent a single domain or bounded context."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Atomic Design"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "span",
                "value": "Atomic design is a methodology for creating design systems. There are five distinct levels in atomic design:"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "numbered",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "span",
                        "value": "Atoms"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "span",
                        "value": "Molecules"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "span",
                        "value": "Organisms"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "span",
                        "value": "Views"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
